CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper July 5, 1968, pg. 1, reads: "Winning Team - Members of the New Pittsburgh Courier editorial staff admire some of the numerous awards won by the newspaper at the 28th annual National Newspaper Publishers Association convention held to New York City. The tall trophy is the Russwurm Award which goes annually to the paper judged to the best in the nation. From left, Carl E. Morris, city managing editor; Ralph E. Koger, staff writer; Charles (Teenie) Harris, award winning photographer and William G. Nunn, Jr., national managing editor."
TitMainTitle: New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper staff: city managing editor Carl E. Morris, staff writer Ralph Koger, photographer Charles "Teenie" Harris, and national managing editor Bill Nunn Jr. posed with trophies from 1968 National Newspaper Publishers Association, posed in Courier office
